<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 25 at 2:29AM CDT until May 25 at 2:45AM CDT by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 245 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN MAVERICK AND WESTERN DIMMIT COUNTIES...
At 228 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 13 miles southeast
of El Indio, moving southeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Carrizo Springs, El Indio, Asherton, Carrizo Hill and Farias Lake.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
